stories.title: West Indies ease to series win
stories.subTitle: West Indies v Zimbabwe, 4th ODI, Bourda
stories.summary: Shivnarine Chanderpaul scored a cathartic 93 in his first match on home soil since being deposed as captain, and Fidel Edwards struck twice with his first four balls of the match, as West Indies toyed with and eventually overwhelmed a substandard Zimbabwe

stories.title: Prospects brighter for Guyana's farewell
stories.subTitle: West Indies v Zimbabwe, 4th ODI, Guyana
stories.summary: The chances of the fourth ODI between West Indies and Zimbabwe actually going ahead increased after a day of good weather on Saturday and Herculean efforts by the groundstaff to get the outfield dry
